          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-4-1723723321663-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is cooked, transfer it to a clean board and shred it apart using two forks – this technique is known as 'pulling'</p><p>Add your <strong>pulled chicken </strong>and any remaining juices to the pan with the <strong>drained sweetcorn</strong> and <strong>gravy stock</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and remove from the heat<strong> </strong>– this is your <strong>pie filling</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-5-1723723328230-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-5-1723723328230-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-5-1723723328230-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-5-1723723328230-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-5-1723723328230-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Transfer the<strong> pie filling</strong> to an<strong> oven-proof dish</strong></p><p>Return the<strong> potatoes</strong> to a low heat with a knob of <strong>butter</strong>, a splash of <strong>milk</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and mash until smooth</p><p>Top the pie filling with the <strong>mashed potato</strong></p><p>Put the dish in the oven for 15-20 min or until everything is bubbling and the mash is golden – this is your <strong>chicken & sweetcorn pie</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-4-1723723332365-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-4-1723723332365-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-4-1723723332365-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-4-1723723332365-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-4-1723723332365-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>When the pie is almost cooked, reboil a full kettle</p><p>Cut your<strong> broccoli</strong> into small florets, discard the stem[s] and leaves</p><p>Add the <strong>broccoli florets</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for 4-5 min or until tender</p><p>Once done, drain, return to the pot, add a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
